3rd class--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
collections:-
   list, tuple, dictionary, set,
list is mutable
start with square brackets
can have duplicates 
can contain any value
index starts with zero
example of a list:-
l1=[1,2,3,4,'a','$']
Len(l1)
l1.remove(2)
l2.append(3)

tuples:--

tuples start with small brackets
it is immutable
allows duplicates

sets:-

sets start and close with flower brackets
it is mutable
it doesn't allow
my_set = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}

dictionary:-

dictionary starts and closes with {}
it has key, values
they are mutable
my_dict = {'name': 'Alice', 'age': 30, 'city': 'New York'}

